&lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;https://walse.cz/opera/20260326-do-aida/images/photo-5.jpg&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“Amore, sommissione, dolcezza” – the traits that Giuseppe Verdi gave his eponymous heroine, Aida, who embodies pure love, tenderness and submissiveness. And these characteristics put her firmly in the tradition of 19th-century female protagonists who were not so much fully rounded personalities as sex objects and a focus for male fantasies, women whose inevitable fate was to die of a broken heart. And Aida is no different.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
